{"questionId":"28508","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Resistor R is connected in a circuit with a cell that has internal resistance.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/84afac67fd13bd630c3b60e279694bf792ddcffb.png\"></p>\n<p>The ammeter and the voltmeter are ideal.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The resistance of R is 50.0 Ω. The voltmeter reads 1.47 V.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Resistor R is replaced by another of resistance 10.0 Ω. The ammeter now reads 139 mA.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the emf of the cell.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>139 × 10<sup>−3 </sup>(10.0 + 0.73)</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>29.4 × 10<sup>−3</sup> (50.0 +&nbsp;0.73) &nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><br>1.49 «V» ✓</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Watch for <strong>ECF</strong> from 5(b)(i).</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"28508","referenceCode":"22N.2.HL.TZ0.5b.iii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the emf of the cell.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.3 – Electric cells","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}